Program: Outlook
Title: Zimbabwean Farm Workers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrqt
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
A look at life for black farm workers in Zimbabwe as attacks on them increase. Also, the art of cutting seaweed from a Scottish gatherer. Chef Shinji Nakamura guests in the studio. An insight into life in La Picota, one of Colombia's highest security jails. Presenter: Heather Payton.